{
  "texts": [
    "For analyses on gaze behavior, the data format stored by SavePreprocessed-Data may be more appropriate: Here, spatial gaze data are transposed using logic in GeometryHelpers to represent how each character gazes in the horizontal and vertical direction relative to another character's eyes.",
    "Condensing data from 3D space onto 2D this way allows to continue data processing in parallel with monitor-based eye-tracking setups (e.g., implementing drift correction and region-of-interest analyses).",
    "Figure 6) shows gaze of the own avatar relative to a partner as well as gaze of the partner relative to the user's own avatar.",
    "Similarly, as in left screen in Fig. 4, the own avatar mostly gazed towards the partner while the partner mostly gazed to its left.",
    "See the folder ExampleData for data and a corresponding R-script."
  ]
}